post_text: The City of Orange Township's food distribution site, formerly at Rosa Parks Community School, has relocated to the Central Park Field House on Lincoln Avenue between Central Avenue and Jackson Street. Superintendent Dr. Gerald Fitzhugh, II, and Councilperson Adrienne Wooten stopped by to visit the new location, staffed by a dedicated team, supporting the effort to provide food to Orange residents in need due to COVID-19. The site operates every Wednesday and Thursday, from 10:00 AM - 2:00 PM, and residents must have a photo ID. Masks are required, and social distancing is observed. Call 973 280-1621 with questions. #GoodtoGreat #FROrange #Census2020 #orangestrongğŸ’ªğŸ¾

post_text: Orange High School acknowledged the Class of 2020 with a drive-through processional yesterday celebrating the accomplishments of each graduate. Superintendent of Schools Dr. Gerald Fitzhugh, II, gave congratulatory remarks. Principal Jason Belton opened the procession of seniors in decorated cars, with horns blowing, balloons flying, and lights flashing to observe the moment. The Orange High School Graduation Ceremony will be virtual this year and streamed on the district's website, social media platforms, and Orange's Channel 35, on Thursday, June 25, at 6:00 p.m. A special note of thanks to English teacher Ms. Thomas for announcing all of the Seniors and to Ms. Halstead and Ms. Budha for leading the charge with the planning and preparation for the Class of 2020. Congratulations graduates! #GoodtoGreat #FROrange #Census2020 #orangestrongğŸ’ªğŸ¾

post_text:
Good Day Orange Public School District Community,

On behalf of the Board of Education, please note that the Board of Education is moving to Virtual Meetings for all Subcommittee Meetings as well as our monthly Board Meeting.

Information to view each meeting will be placed on the district website at www.orange.k12.nj.us. If you are interested in submitting real-time Public Comments or Questions during the Virtual Meeting broadcasts, an email address will also be provided on the website to do.

The following meetings are scheduled for public viewing:
Curriculum and Instruction Committee Meeting: March 31, 2020, at 3:30 PM
Finance Committee Meeting: April 2, 2020, at 5:30 PM
Facilities Committee Meeting: April 6, 2020, at 2:30 PM
Regular Board Meeting: April 7, 2020, at 7:30 PM

Thank you,

Dr. Gerald Fitzhugh, II
Superintendent of Schools

#GoodtoGreat #FROrange #Census2020 #orangestrongğŸ’ªğŸ¾
